## Changes: `src/safety.rs` (142 insertions)

### 1. `check_unbounded_command` function (new)
Detects three categories of unbounded commands before execution:
• **`find /` / `find ~`** without `-maxdepth` — scans the entire filesystem
• **`grep -r /` / `grep -r ~`** — recursive grep from root/home (including combined flags like `-ri`, `-rn`)
• **`rg pattern /` / `rg pattern ~`** — ripgrep searching root/home as a path

### 2. `is_root_or_home` helper (new)
Matches `/`, `~`, `~/`, `$HOME`, `$HOME/`, `${HOME}`, `${HOME}/`.

### 3. Wiring into `analyze_bash_command`
Added as check #27, after `check_systemctl_mask`. Follows the same pattern as all other checks.

### 4. Three new test functions
• `test_analyze_unbounded_find` — 18 assertions (unbounded: flagged; bounded with `-maxdepth`: safe; subdirectory paths: safe)
• `test_analyze_unbounded_grep_recursive` — 12 assertions (recursive from root: flagged; recursive from subdirectory: safe; non-recursive grep: safe)
• `test_analyze_unbounded_ripgrep` — 11 assertions (root/home path: flagged; subdirectory/cwd: safe; `rg /` without pattern: safe — treated as pattern search in cwd)

